abstract: The Times spoke to Mr. Richmond, a Louisiana congressman and former chair of the Congressional Black Caucus, about his role with the campaign and the 1994 crime bill.
snippet: The Times spoke to Mr. Richmond, a Louisiana congressman and former chair of the Congressional Black Caucus, about his role with the campaign and the 1994 crime bill.
lead_paragraph: Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidential campaign is naming Representative Cedric Richmond to a major leadership role within the organization, a move that could bolster Mr. Biden’s standing with some congressional Democrats and African-American leaders in politically important states, even as the former vice president faces scrutiny over his record on criminal justice issues.

abstract: A threshold of 130,000 donors will force campaigns to spend more on digital ads they hope will go viral, an expensive redirection of resources, some campaigns said.
snippet: A threshold of 130,000 donors will force campaigns to spend more on digital ads they hope will go viral, an expensive redirection of resources, some campaigns said.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic Party’s new directive that candidates must have at least 130,000 donors to qualify for the third primary debate in September arrived virtually without warning on Wednesday morning, and immediately sent shock waves through presidential campaigns worried that it would distort their priorities and affect the way they operate.

abstract: Robert S. Mueller III stated clearly that he hoped his public statement Wednesday would be his last, but with impeachment fever rising, Democrats want him on a witness stand.
snippet: Robert S. Mueller III stated clearly that he hoped his public statement Wednesday would be his last, but with impeachment fever rising, Democrats want him on a witness stand.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic House leaders brushed aside Robert S. Mueller III’s clear reluctance to testify before Congress on Wednesday and said they would call him anyway, hoping to give the House’s investigation of President Trump a lift even as several senior Democrats joined the rising clamor to begin impeachment proceedings.

abstract: Previously, only a few candidates had called for beginning impeachment proceedings against President Trump. Now, a majority of the Democratic field has expressed support.
snippet: Previously, only a few candidates had called for beginning impeachment proceedings against President Trump. Now, a majority of the Democratic field has expressed support.
lead_paragraph: Robert S. Mueller III’s statement on Wednesday, in which he reiterated the conclusions of his investigation and declined to clear President Trump, seemed to open a dam in the Democratic presidential field.

abstract: For debate No. 3, in mid-September, candidates must have donations from 130,000 people and register at least 2 percent in four polls.
snippet: For debate No. 3, in mid-September, candidates must have donations from 130,000 people and register at least 2 percent in four polls.
lead_paragraph: The national Democratic Party will toughen the requirements for participating in the presidential primary debates this fall, a decision likely to prompt blowback from candidates struggling to gain a foothold in the crowded race.
